User Stories
1. Table Reservations:

As a customer, I want to reserve a table through an online platform so that I can guarantee my place ahead of time.
As a manager, I want to access and manage reservation records so that I can maintain an accurate overview of table availability.
As a customer, I want to be notified with a booking confirmation and upcoming reminders so that I remain informed about my reservation.
-As a customer, I want to specify special requests (e.g., dietary preferences or celebrations) while booking so that my needs are met.

2.Order Management:
As a waiter, I want to submit orders through a digital interface so that the kitchen staff receives them instantly.
As a chef, I want to change the status of orders so that serving staff can be informed when meals are prepared and ready.
As a waiter, I want to edit or remove an order following its submission so that any customer adjustments can be handled efficiently.
As a manager, I want to monitor the time taken to fulfill orders so that I can detect and address any workflow delays.

3.Inventory Tracking:
As a manager, I want to keep track of current stock levels so that replenishment can be arranged before supplies are depleted.
As a chef, I want to receive notifications when ingredients are running low so that I can adjust meal planning in advance.
As a manager, I want to produce detailed reports on stock consumption so that I can minimize waste and improve cost management.
As a supplier, I want to automatically receive purchase requests when inventory falls below a set threshold so that prompt delivery can be ensured.

4.Financial Reporting:
As a manager, I want to produce end-of-day sales summaries so that I can evaluate the restaurant's daily performance and earnings.
As an owner, I want to access profit and loss overviews so that I can assess the overall financial condition of the business.
As a manager, I want to examine and compare sales figures across different weeks or months so that I can pinpoint periods of high and low performance.
As a manager, I want to review data on best-selling menu items so that I can design targeted promotional strategies.

5.Employee Scheduling:
As an admin, I want to allocate work shifts to staff members so that the workforce is efficiently distributed.
As an employee, I want to have early access to my upcoming schedule so that I can organize my personal commitments accordingly.
As an employee, I want to submit requests for shift changes or exchanges so that I can maintain a healthy work-life balance.
As a manager, I want to monitor staff attendance records so that shift coverage is maintained and payroll is processed correctly.

6.Customer Feedback:
As a customer, I want to submit a review of my overall dining experience so that the restaurant can be informed of my impressions.
As a manager, I want to collect and review customer feedback so that recurring issues can be identified and service standards can be raised.
As a customer, I want to leave ratings for specific dishes so that other diners can benefit from my recommendations and the menu can be shaped accordingly.

7.Payment and Billing:
As a customer, I want the option to divide the total bill among several guests so that each person pays their individual portion.
As a cashier, I want to handle various payment methods including cash, card, and digital wallets so that all customer payment preferences are supported.
As a manager, I want to monitor unresolved bills or payment disputes so that they can be addressed and closed in a timely manner.
